args: *yaaaawn* It's morning already,\nbut I managed to get it done...
One hand-knit sweater,\nall wrapped and ready to go!
Now to get to work on the other gift.\nBetter wait for nightfall for that...
Oh, good! Looks like I'm alone.
Cleo banned me from the kitchen because\nI cause problems for others, but if others\naren't here, I can't CAUSE them problems!
Although I might be skating by\non a technicality here...
But whatever! I have to make these\ncupcakes for him, and they need to be\njam-packed with all my gratitude!
Better get to it and finish this thing\nbefore anyone notices I'm here. \nOn my mark...get set...bake!
Hrm... It won't come together no matter\nhow much I mix it. I guess it SHOULD\ntaste okay, but... *lick*
Gah! Sweet! So sweet! Gosh darn it,\nI mixed up flour with sugar again.
Now I'll whip this cream until it's light and\nairy with stiff peaks... AAAAAH!
Dang it! The bowl slipped\nout of my fingers!
Okay, the batter looks good! Let's take\na peek and see if it's cooked through...
ACK! I poked it with a skewer to check\nthe inside and it exploded! Whyyyyy?!
*sigh* This has been a complete disaster.\nI'm sure no star baker...
Now I'm running low on ingredients and\nthe sun is almost up. Maybe I should just\nthrow in the tea towel already...
No! I need to see this through!
My master said one of my strengths is\nthat I always see the bright side of things!
If I gave up now, I'd be giving up the\nstrength he discovered in me!
Looks like I have just enough ingredients\nfor one more shot at this...
I have to get it right this time. I can't fail!
*sigh* You're forgetting that you very\nspecifically fail when you're overly eager.
Philia! Cibella! Why are you here?
We dropped by your room to give you a\npep talk for tomorrow and found you gone.\nThis was the first place we thought to look.
Honestly, if you're already messing up this\nmuch, you should have talked to me.\nI told you I'd help, remember?

Look, if you just stand there with a mouth
hanging open, it's gonna be morning
before you know it. Where's your recipe?
Let's team up and get the cupcakes baked!
And a single dollop of cream and...\nThere! Perfection incarnate.
Er, mine's not much to look at,\nbut at least it's done!
I'll just put them in this box, tie it up\nwith a ribbon, and we're good to go!
I can't thank you two enough.
Happy to help! Also, I took the liberty of\ncunningly loading my treat full of my OWN\nlove for the prince. Heh heh heh...
The prince has done much for me as well,\nso I tried to instill that sense of gratitude\ninto my own confection.
All that's left is for you to hand it over!
She fell asleep standing up.\nThat's impressive.
Little wonder, considering she made a\nplan, knit a sweater, and stayed up\nall night baking for the past two days.
*sigh* Should we carry her to her room?
We'll need to keep watch and wake her\nin the morning, lest she oversleep and\nmake a big kerfuffle.
Sounds good.\nTomorrow, the day of destiny arrives!
Um, how do I look? My going-out hat\nisn't crooked or anything, right?
You cut a dashing figure. Not a lock of\nhair out of place or a stray bit of fuzz\nto be found anywhere.
Okay, good. Well...off I go, I guess.
Take care. And do have fun!
If you bork things up with the prince,\nI'll never let you hear the end of it!
Got it! I'm gonna make this dateNO!\nIt's NOT a date, DORKUS!
I'm gonna make this OUTING\na smashing success!
I think she just fell down the stairs.
*sigh* She is predictable if nothing else.
